Changing your work packages view 
  Sort or filter your view to see only those work packages in which
	 you are interested. 
   
   
	  
		On the Work Packages tab, there can
		  be a long list of work packages in various states of the work flow. You can
		  filter this list to see only the work packages in which you are interested or
		  you can sort the list to see the work packages in a specified order. You can
		  sort and filter using options such as assignment status, name, due date, and
		  feature. 
		 
	  
	  
		 
		   Click the 
			 Work Packages tab. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Sort the list of work packages by clicking 
			 Sort, and then selecting an option. 
		   
		  The list of work packages is sorted based on the option
			 selected. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Filter the list of work packages: 
		   
		   
			  
				Select the desired filter options. 
				 
			  
			  
				Click 
				  Apply Filters. 
				 
				The list of work packages is filtered and only work
				  packages that meet the selected options are displayed. 
				 
			  
		   
		 
		 
		  Unfilter the list of work packages: 
		   
		   
			  
				Click 
				  Clear above the filter options. 
				 
			  
			  
				Click 
				  Apply Filters. 
				 
				The complete list of work packages is displayed. 
				 
			  
		   
		 
	  
	  
		 The list of work packages is
		  changed based on your selection. 
		 
	  
	  
		Example situation 
		You might want to see all
		  outstanding work packages that impact a certain deliverable. In this case,
		  using the filters, select the desired 
		  Asset and 
		  Work States (every state except 
		  Complete), and then click 
		  Apply Filters. 
		 
	  
   
